~ contract_1
do BaseDialogueManager.dialogue_activated.emit()
Gabbi: You really came back for this place?
- What should I do first?
	Gabbi: Start small.
	Gabbi: People do not need big promises right now. They need something real.
	Gabbi: Food, work, a roof that does not fall apart. Start there.
	do BaseDialogueManager.dialogue_deactivated.emit()
	=> END
- How are people doing?
	Gabbi: Tired. Careful. Broke.
	Gabbi: Some still want this city to stand again.
	Gabbi: They just do not trust words anymore.
	do BaseDialogueManager.dialogue_deactivated.emit()
	=> END
- I will come back later.
	Gabbi: Do not take too long.
	do BaseDialogueManager.dialogue_deactivated.emit()
	=> END

~ intro_gabbi_1
do BaseDialogueManager.dialogue_activated.emit()
Gabbi: Hi there! Welcome to Time is Precious.
Gabbi: It is a 2D pixel management RPG about time, work, resources, and choices.
Gabbi: Every decision is part of building a better life.
=> gabbi_intro_questions_first

~ gabbi_intro_questions_first
Gabbi: What would you like to know first?
- Can you tell me more about this?
	Gabbi: You gather materials, meet villagers, and manage your day.
	Gabbi: Step by step, you help this village grow.
	=> gabbi_intro_questions_more
- What makes this game different?
	Gabbi: The village is meant to feel like more than a background.
	Gabbi: Some characters are planned to respond in more personal and unexpected ways as the game develops.
	=> gabbi_intro_questions_more
- When will the game be released?
	Gabbi: The playable prototype is planned to be available as early as the end of 2026.
	=> gabbi_intro_questions_more
- Where can we play it?
	Gabbi: The plan is to make it playable on Android and PC.
	=> gabbi_intro_questions_more
- I am ready to begin.
	Gabbi: It is still early, but every step brings the world closer to life.
	Gabbi: One percent at a time.
	do BaseDialogueManager.dialogue_deactivated.emit()
	=> END

